Acknowledgements
================================================================================

This sample is built on top of, and inspired by, official AWS reference
material and open-source AWS Labs projects. The structure of the CDC
pipeline (DSQL native CDC → Kinesis → Lambda → Redshift) is derived from
patterns published by AWS.

Primary references:

* "Getting started with Change Data Capture in Amazon Aurora DSQL"
  by Vijay Karumajji, AWS Database Blog, May 2026.
  https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/database/getting-started-with-change-data-capture-in-amazon-aurora-dsql/
  The DSQL CDC setup commands, IAM trust policy template, and CDC event
  format documentation in this repository are adapted from this post.

* "Accelerating SQL analytics with Amazon Redshift MCP server"
  AWS Big Data Blog.
  https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/big-data/accelerating-sql-analytics-with-amazon-redshift-mcp-server/

* awslabs/agent-plugins
  https://github.com/awslabs/agent-plugins
  The `databases-on-aws` plugin / `dsql` agent skill referenced in the
  blog post is published by AWS Labs under Apache 2.0.

* awslabs/mcp
  https://github.com/awslabs/mcp
  The Aurora DSQL MCP server (src/aurora-dsql-mcp-server) and Redshift
  MCP server (src/redshift-mcp-server) referenced in the blog post are
  published by AWS Labs under Apache 2.0. The DSQL schema in this sample
  was validated using the `dsql_lint` tool from the Aurora DSQL MCP server.

* AWS Aurora DSQL documentation
  https://docs.aws.amazon.com/aurora-dsql/latest/userguide/cdc-streams.html

* Amazon Redshift documentation
  https://docs.aws.amazon.com/redshift/

